ult in very unequal outcomes. This book is essential reading for researchers, students and practitioners interested in the late careers and the future of retirement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aOld age pensionsxGovernment policyzGreat Britain. 0aOld age pensionsxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aRetirement agexGovernment policyzGreat Britain. 0aRetirement agexGovernment policyzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311119643540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447326205423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447326205/original  a978-3-11-119643-5  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles